Happy December 1st! 🎄🕎🎄🕎🎄⁣
Let me set the scene… 💭💭⁣
Mariah Carey’s playing on every radio station, Home Alone is on repeat, and everyone is cozy around the fireplace, drinking a big’ old mug of delicious hot chocolate…🎄🎶🎥 🔥🍫🎄… except this time, it’s a hot chocolate KINDER BOMB! 🍫 ☕️ 💣⁣
 ⁣
I made these bombs last year, and they did not disappoint! They are super fun for the holiday season, and using a Kinder Egg is absolutely genius! 🧠 ⁣
⁣
What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
* Kinder surprise egg⁣
* 2 tsp hot chocolate mix ⁣
* mini marshmallows (I use @mydandies available at @naturesante 
* Toppings: White chocolate, sprinkles ⁣
* Hot milk of choice⁣
⁣
Make it:⁣
* Unwrap your kinder egg end gently break the egg in half. (Use a sharp knife along the seal of the two chocolate sides to gently split. Set toy aside.⁣
* Add hot cocoa powder to one side of the egg, along with some mini marshmallows. ⁣
* Heat a pan on the stove and gently press the other half of the chocolate egg on the pan for 2-3 seconds.⁣
* Gently press the empty chocolate egg over the filled egg and seal. ⁣
* Melt White chocolate and drizzle over filled kinder egg. Sprinkle with sprinkles! 🌈 ⁣
* Add the kinder hot chocolate bomb to a glass and pour your milk of choice.⁣
⁣
Enjoy! 😘 #wiseEATS ⁣

HOT HONEY CHICKEN FTW!! 🏆 This dish is absolutely delish!! ⁣
It’s spicy 🥵 ⁣
It’s sticky 🍯 ⁣
It’s juicy 💦 ⁣
…and it’s deeelish! 💯 Also, it takes no time at all to prepare! ⁣
It’s a MUST MAKE situation! 🤤 ⁣
⁣
Oh, and if spicy 🌶️ isn’t your thing, just use regular honey! ⁣
⁣
Recipe inspo @peaslovencarrots 
What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
8-10 pieces of chicken (I used dark meat from @smoothiesgomarche)
3 tbsp olive oil ⁣
1/2 cup hot honey (I used @drizzle_honey hot honey)⁣
8 garlic cloves, minced⁣
1 tbsp apple cider vinegar ⁣
2 tsp kosher Salt⁣
1 tsp pepper⁣
2 tsp garlic powder⁣
1+1/2 tsp onion powder⁣
1 tsp oregano⁣
2 tsp parsley (fresh or dried)⁣
⁣
Make it:⁣
* Start by preheating your oven to 350°F. ⁣
* Grab a bowl and mix together all the ingredients listed above.⁣
* Place the chicken in a large glass baking dish and pour marinade over chicken. ⁣Let marinate for at least 3-4 hours, or even overnight.
* Make sure to cover the pyrex tightly with parchment and then foil.⁣
* Bake in the oven for 1 hour, then uncover the dish and baste chicken with the juices.⁣ Cook for another 20 minutes, basting every few minutes until nice and golden brown.⁣
* Serve with rice, potatoes or even couscous!⁣
⁣

My favourite dish to order as a kid was always a Caprese salad 🍅🧀 ⁣Loved it! 😋 ⁣
I still do but let’s be honest… it was never about the tomatoes and cheese 🙅🏻‍♀️… What made me order this dish time and time again, we’re the yummy juices that accumulate on the bottom of the plate from the mixing of the tomatoes, fresh cheese and of course a delicious and flavourful olive oil 💯💯💯⁣ I’d mop that shit up with a crusty baguette, like it was nobody’s business! 😆😋 

This is the perfect appetizer for any upcoming holiday get together you may be having! Don’t forget to buy a baguette and toast it up for all that mopping 🤤 🥖🤤
⁣
ROASTED CAPRESE SALAD 🍅🧀 ⁣
What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
* 1 pint cherry tomatoes⁣
* 3 garlic cloves, smashed⁣
* 3 sprigs thyme⁣
* 1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil⁣
* Kosher salt⁣
* 8oz. fresh buffalo mozzarella, ripped into big pieces⁣
* Flaky sea salt⁣
* Baguette, brushed with oil, toasted in oven (for serving)⁣
⁣
Make it: ⁣
* Preheat oven to 350°F. ⁣
* Mix tomatoes, garlic, thyme, and olive oil on a rimmed baking sheet to coat, and season with kosher salt. ⁣
* Spread tomatoes out in a single layer and roast until tomatoes are bursting and lightly charred, 45 minutes. Once done let cool.⁣
* Arrange ripped mozzarella on a platter and spoon warm tomato juices over; sprinkle with sea salt. ⁣
* Toasted baguette for soaking up all those deeelicious juices.⁣
⁣
⁣
Enjoy! 😘 #wiseEATS⁣

Joe and the Juice COPYCAT BREAD! 🥖
Maybe the most coveted bread on the planet right now 😂!! 
Sounds extreme I know, but if you are in the know, then YOU KNOW the @joeandthejuice TUNACADO sandwich has gone VIRAL!!! 
I needed to make this sandwich the moment I saw that it had gone viral, except I tried for weeks to find this iconic thin flat bread and friends… I’m here’s to tell you, there ain’t nothing like it here in Canada 🇨🇦! 
So that’s where I come in… 👋🏼 
Let’s recreate this iconic sandwich starting with the bread!! 
 🎞️This reel is dedicated solely to the bread… Tomorrow I’ll drop the sandwich deets 🥪 

DO IT! 💯 
Recipe adapted from @marwaibraheem10
What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* 3.5 cups whole wheat flour
* 1 tbsp active dry yeast
* 1 tbsp sugar
* 2 cups warm water
* 1 tsp salt
* 1 tsp baking powder
* 1/8 cup olive oil

Make it:
* In a large mixing bowl, add in the whole wheat flour, active dry yeast, sugar, salt and baking powder. Mix well.
* Transfer the flour mix into a KitchenAid mixer, fitted with a dough hook.
* Pour in the warm water and then the olive oil, and mix. Mix for 5-7 minutes until a sticky dough is formed
* When it’s done, transfer the dough to an oiled bowl. (I used olive oil). Cover with plastic wrap and then with a dish towel. Place in warm spot to proof for 2 hours.
* After the two hours, the dough should double in size.
* Next, oil a 12 x 17 baking tray using a silicon brush and transfer the dough onto the tray.
* Spread the dough evenly to surround the entire tray.
* Using a oiled knife (see reel), score the dough to desired size.
* Use your fingertips to make dimples, just like the real Joe and the juice bread 
* Next, poke it with a fork to make sure no air pockets form while it’s baking.
* Now, set the dough aside for 15 minutes while you preheat the oven to 450°F
* Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes.
* When ready, remove from the oven and go over the original scores with your knife to properly cut out the bread.
* If using right away, slice down the middle, and enjoy with whatever you’d like, or, if you were going to freeze them, wrap each one in plastic wrap and place in a Ziploc bag and into the freezer.
Enjoy! 😘#wiseEATS

UPGRADED BUTTERED NOODS 🧈🍝 💯 ⁣
This classic dish that kids ask for all the time is delicious of course, but as you can imagine, has very little nutritional value. ⁣
Now with the addition of brussels sprout leaves, you can feel a teensy bit better knowing that your kids are eating not just buttered noodles, but buttered noodles with a side of veggies 💚! The brussels sprouts cook super quickly and a add a gorgeous vibrance to the dish! Plus they actually taste so delicious this way! 😋 ⁣
⁣
Make it!!⁣
⁣
What you’ll need:⁣
* 1 1/2 cups brussels sprouts leaves⁣
* 12 ounces any small noodle⁣
* kosher salt⁣
* 1 stick unsalted butter⁣
* 1/2 cup grated parmesan (or more)⁣
* salt and pepper to taste⁣
⁣
Make it⁣
* Start by cutting the stems off of each sprout and then cut each one in half. Then slowly separate and peel each layer off. When you get to the centre and can’t peel anymore, slice the core.⁣
* Bring a large pot of water on to boil. Add kosher salt and make it taste like the sea 🌊 ⁣
* Meanwhile, melt the butter over medium heat. Once the butter begins turning brown and smelling nutty, turn off the heat. Set aside for a few mins. ⁣
* Check the cooking time of the pasta you are using. Set the timer for one minute less than the time recommended for al dente. When the time is up on your noodles, add in your brussels sprouts and cook for 1 minute more. ‼️Reserve at least 1 cup of the cooking liquid and set aside‼️⁣
* Drain the pasta/sprouts. Place cooked and drain pasta back into the hot pot.⁣
* Bring the brown butter back up to temperature over medium heat and pour the butter over the pasta/sprouts. Add in a 1/2 cup of the reserved cooking liquid and the parmesan. Adjust with the salt and pepper to taste. If necessary, add some more of the pasta water/ parm to the pot.⁣
⁣
Enjoy! 😘 #wiseEATS⁣

Omgawd 🤯 
This schnitzel was off the charts!📈 Super crunchy and crispy outside, yet tender and juicy on the inside. Bet you wouldn’t believe it’s baked! 😱 Yes, that’s right, BAKED! 🙌🏼 
The trick is to pan fry the panko breadcrumbs beforehand, let them cool, then bread your raw chicken and bake. Totally genius! 💯 
Now go make it! 😜
Recipe adapted from @bonapetit
What you’ll need:
* 6 boneless, skinless chicken thighs or 3 boneless, skinless breasts 
* 1 egg yolk
* 3 tbsp mayonnaise
* 1 tbsp Dijon mustard
* ¾ teaspoon kosher salt
* Freshly ground black pepper
* ½ cup olive oil
* 2 cups panko 
* 1 tbsp honey
* Pinch of cayenne pepper
* 3 tbsp finely chopped chives
Honey Mustard DIP:
* ¼ cup mayonnaise, ¼ cup Dijon mustard, 3 tbsp chives, chopped, 1 tbsp honey, pinch of cayenne, and fresh pepper.
Lets make it:
* Position a rack in centre of oven and preheat to 450°F. Place a wire rack inside a rimmed baking sheet. Place chicken on rack, then pat dry with paper towels.
* Whisk egg yolk, mayonnaise, Dijon mustard, salt, and several cranks of black pepper in a large bowl until smooth. Add chicken to bowl and turn pieces several times with tongs until evenly coated.
* Heat olive oil in a medium skillet over medium. I used a cast iron. Test oil to see if it’s hot enough by adding a pinch of panko. If tiny bubbles appear instantly around each bit of panko, you’re good to go. Add remaining panko and cook, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon, until crumbs are golden brown, about 5 minutes. 
* Remove skillet from heat and let cool several minutes. Place skillet on work surface next to bowl of chicken and wire rack.
* Using tongs, take 1 piece of chicken at a time and place in skillet. Using 1 hand, pat toasted panko over top of thigh, pressing firmly to stick. Turn chicken and repeat on other side with more crumbs. Lightly shake off excess crumbs. Transfer chicken to wire rack. Repeat with remaining chicken pieces.
* Transfer sheet to oven and bake chicken until fully cooked through, juices run clear when pierced with a knife, and breadcrumbs are golden deep brown, 15–20 minutes.

20 minutes 🌶️SPICY KIMCHI TOFU STEW 🥵 
This soup packs a punch 🤜🏼 in the best way possible. It’s so warm and comforting, yet delicious and satisfying! Most of these ingredients you can find at your grocery store, but some you may have to travel to your local Asian market. I’m here to tell you, it’s worth the trip! 🏃‍♀️ 

Make it! 💯 
Adapted from @tiffy.cooks 

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
4-5 dry shiitake mushrooms (optional)
1 tbsp of Gochujang (Korean fermented red pepper paste)
5 cloves of garlic (minced) 
1 tbsp of light soy sauce
1 tbsp of coconut sugar  
2 tsp Gochugaru (Korean chilli flakes)
1 tsp of black pepper 
1/2 pack of soft silken Tofu 
3 tbsp of chopped Kimchi 
4 cups of chicken stock (or veg)
1 cup of Korean rice cakes (frozen) or use ramen noodles
1 Egg 

Make it:
1. Start by covering your mushrooms in boiling water and soak for 20 minutes.
2. Next, make the spicy garlic paste in a bowl. Using a whisk, mix the gochujang, soy sauce, sugar, gochugaru, black pepper, and minced garlic. Set aside.
3. In a pot, add kimchi and your prepared spicy garlic paste. Mix well. Then add in 4 cups of stock. Turn the heat up to medium-high and bring it to a simmer.
4. Squeeze your shiitake mushrooms and try and extract as much water as possible. Then slice and add to broth.
5. Add in your rice cakes or ramen noodles and cook for 2 minutes. 
5. Add in silken tofu and cook for another 2-3 minutes. 
6. When bubbling and boiling, crack in an egg and cover for 2 mins. Garnish with cilantro or green onion. Enjoy right away with some steamed rice to cut the heat! 🤤 

Enjoy! 😘 #wiseEATS

Nothing like a good pasta night! ⁣🍝🙌🏼💯 This one was 😚😚😚 *chef’s kiss*⁣… 
You need to make it! ⁣🤤
⁣
What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
Chicken 🍗:⁣
* 3 boneless, skinless chicken breasts, chopped into bite size cubes⁣
* 1/2 tsp each garlic powder/ onion powder and smoked paprika⁣
* 1/2 tsp @kanelspices holy grail Garlic salt ⁣
* Pepper to taste⁣
* 1 tbsp olive oil⁣
⁣
Pasta 🍝:⁣
* 1 tbsp unsalted butter⁣
* 1 tbsp olive oil⁣
* 1 small onion, chopped ⁣
* 1 small shallot, chopped⁣
* 8 oz. Cremini mushrooms, sliced⁣
* 3 garlic cloves, minced⁣
* 1/4 cup tomato paste⁣
* 1/4 cup cooking cream⁣
* 8 oz. Fettuccini + starchy water⁣
* 1/4 Parmesan cheese ⁣
* Fresh basil ⁣
⁣
Make it:⁣
* Cook the pasta according to package instructions until it’s al dente. Don’t forget the soldier Pass the water! The water should taste like to sea 🌊. 
‼️Reserve one cup of pasta water BEFORE DRAINING and set aside. 
* Meanwhile, place cubed chicken in a bowl and coat with one tbsp of olive oil and the garlic, onion and paprkia spices. Mix well. ⁣
* Cook chicken on medium high heat in a large skillet. Cook until the chicken is no longer pink.., should take about 5 minutes. Remove and set aside ⁣
* In the same dirty pan, add in the butter and one tablespoon of olive oil. Add in onions, shallots and mushrooms and sauté for a few minutes, until the mushrooms start to sweat and release their moisture.⁣
* Next, add in the tomato paste and use a wooden spoon to break it down. Let the tomato paste cook down for at least five minutes.⁣
* Pour in the cream and mix well. ⁣
* Add back the cooked chicken.⁣
* Lastly, add in your cooked pasta, as well as the reserved pasta water, parmesan cheese and mix well. Garnish with fresh basil, more parmesan and enjoy right away! 😚 ⁣
⁣
Enjoy! 😘 #wiseEATS⁣

Omg omg this soup!!! Sooooooo good!!! 🤤🔥 Just a couple of 🔑 things to note when making the soup:
📌Use 2 portugese sausages (I got mine at @lemaitreboucher) they add just the right amount of smokey flavour 💨 
📌Use ALL the spices I listed below.. trust 🙌🏼
📌Go in with a handheld blender if you have,..give it a whizz or 2. It makes for a thick and delicious consistency 💯
📌Don’t forget to add the Parmesan rind!! 🧀Also don’t forget to take it out before serving!
Ok.. now go make it and tag meeeee!! 🙌🏼💯

Sausage, Chicken and Pinto Bean Soup 🫘 

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* 2 tbsp olive oil
* 1 small onion, diced
* 1 large leek, sliced thin in half moons
* 2 carrots, diced
* 2 ribs celery, diced
* 3 cloves garlic, minced
* 2 Portuguese sausage, hot or mild
* 1 lbs. minced chicken
* 2 (15.5 oz.) cans Pinto Beans, drained and rinsed
* 1 tsp dried basil
* 1 tsp dried parsley
* 1/2 tsp oregano
* 1/2 tsp mustard powder
* 1/4 tsp pepper
* 1 tsp hot sauce (I used @cholulahotsauce)
* 6 cups low sodium chicken broth
* Parmesan rind (optional but of so good!)
* 3 cups spinach or kale
* Freshly grated Parmesan cheese, optional
* toasted baguette for serving
Make it:
* Start by preparing you veggies. Dice the onion, carrots and celery. Slice the leek and mince the garlic. 
* Remove the casings from the sausage and set aside.
* Drain the two cans of beans and set aside.
* Preheat a large pot over medium heat. Add the sausage and cook and crumble to break it apart. Next, add in the minced chicken and continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until the meat is cooked through. It’ll take around 8-10 minutes.
* Remove the sausage and chicken from the pot and set aside. 
* To the dirty pot, add 1 tbsp of olive oil 
* Add the diced onions, celery, carrots and leek. Cook for 5 minutes. Next, add the dry basil, parsley, oregano, mustard powder, pepper and hot sauce. Mix well.
* Add in the fresh garlic and stir. 
* Add the chicken broth and use a spatula to “clean” the bottom of the pot, this will add more flavour to the soup. 
* Add in the beans and bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Simmer for 20 minutes.

This asian style pasta is DEEEEEELISHHHHH!! 😋Seasoned with the pan drippings from the Vietnamese style shrimps, plus soy, spicy chili oil and a hint of butter…. Dayyuuummm! 💯 
I kinda made it up, but it is definitely a keeper!! Best news of all, it’s ready in 15 minutes!!! ⏱ ⁣
Try it out!!⁣ 🤤🤤🤤
⁣
What you’ll need:⁣👩🏻‍🍳
* 1 tbsp kosher salt for pasta⁣
* 12 oz box of spaghetti ⁣
* 1 box of organic kale or baby spinach⁣
* 2 garlics, sliced⁣
* 1 tbsp unsalted butter⁣
* 1 heaping tbsp of chili onion crunch or samba oelek or any chili garlic oil.⁣
* 1-2 tbsp low sodium soy sauce⁣

It’s the most minimal soup with the most maximum flavour. The secret is all in the method people…Make it!⁣

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
* 3 tbsp olive oil⁣
* 1 medium onion (6 ounces), sliced thin⁣
* 1 head fresh cauliflower (about 1-1/2 lbs), broken into florets⁣
* Salt, to taste⁣
* 5 1/2 cups water, divided⁣
* Freshly ground black pepper⁣
Optional topping:⁣
* 4 fresh garlics, sliced thin for chips ⁣
* 2 tbsp capers, drained⁣
* 3 tbsp avocado oil⁣
⁣
Make it:⁣
* Warm the olive oil in a heavy-bottomed pan. Sweat the onion in the olive oil over low heat without letting it brown for 15 minutes.⁣
* Add the cauliflower, salt to taste, and 1/2 cup water. Raise the heat slightly, cover the pot tightly and stew the cauliflower for 15 to 18 minutes, or until tender. Then add another 4 1/2 cups hot water, bring to a low simmer and cook an additional 20 minutes uncovered.⁣
* Meanwhile, add your avocado oil to a small sauce, pan and fry the garlic chips and capers, for about four minutes. Always watch! 👀 They can burn easily!!🔥 When golden brown, drain in a strainer, saving the infused oil. Set both chips and oil aside.⁣
* Purée the soup using a handheld blender if you have. If not, blend in batches using a blender. Let the soup stand for 20 minutes. In this time it will thicken slightly.⁣
* Thin the soup with 1/2 cup hot water. Reheat the soup. Serve hot, topped with fried garlic and capers chips, and drizzled with a little of the infused oil. 🤤 ⁣

Hello there 👋, how do you STEW? Man, that’s so bad but I couldn’t resist 🤓! These cold winter nights call for some hardcore comfort food. Something STEWpendous  perhaps? 🤓🤓🤓🤣 Ok I’ll stop. 
Nothing quite sticks to your bones like stew 🥩🥔🥕. 
Thick, meaty, stew. It takes a bit of time to make ⏱, but it’s well worth the wait!! 💯 

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* 3 lbs boneless beef chuck (well-marbled), cut into 1-1/2-inch pieces available @smoothiesgomarche 
* 2 tsp salt
* 1 tsp pepper
* 3 tbsp olive oil
* 2 yellow onions, cut into 1-inch chunks
* 7 cloves garlic, peeled and smashed
* 2 tbsp balsamic vinegar
* 1-1/2 tbsp tomato paste
* 1/4 cup all-purpose flour
* 2 cups dry red wine 
* 2 cups beef broth
* 2 cups water
* 1 bay leaf
* 1/2 teaspoon dried thyme
* 1-1/2 teaspoons sugar
* 4 large carrots, peeled and cut into one-inch chunks 
* 1 lbs small white boiling potatoes (baby yukons), cut in half
* Fresh chopped parsley, for serving
Make it: 
📌 Preheat the oven to 325°F and set a rack in the lower middle position.
📌 Pat the beef dry and season with the salt and pepper. In a large Dutch oven or heavy soup pot, heat 1 tablespoon of the olive oil over medium-high heat until hot and shimmering. Brown the meat in batches, turning with tongs, for about 5 minutes per batch; add more oil for each batch. Transfer the meat to a plate and set aside.
📌 Add the onions, garlic and balsamic vinegar and cook, stirring with a wooden spoon and scraping the brown bits from bottom of the pan, for about 5 minutes. 
📌 Add the tomato paste and cook for a minute more. Add the seared beef with its juices back to the pan and sprinkle with the flour. Stir with wooden spoon until the flour is dissolved, 1 to 2 minutes. 
📌 Add the wine, beef broth, water, bay leaf, thyme, and sugar. Stir with a wooden spoon to loosen any brown bits from the bottom of the pan and bring to a boil. 
📌 Cover the pot with a lid, transfer to the oven, and braise for 1-2 hours.
📌 Remove the pot from the oven and add the carrots and potatoes 🥕🥔. Cover and place back in oven for another hour or so. Taste and adjust seasoning if necessary. 
📌Serve as is or over noodles. Garnish with fresh parsley.

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* 1 (4-inch) piece fresh ginger, peeled
* 6 garlic cloves, peeled
* 1 jalapeño
* 2 pounds ground chicken
* 1 large bunch cilantro, leaves and stems finely chopped, a few whole leaves reserved for serving
* 3 tbsp fish sauce
* Kosher salt
* 2 tbsp vegetable or coconut oil, plus more as needed

* ½ teaspoon granulated sugar

1. Using the small holes of a box grater, or a Microplane, grate the ginger, garlic and jalapeño (or finely chop them by hand). Transfer half to a large bowl and set the rest aside. To the large bowl, add the chicken, finely chopped cilantro, 2 tablespoons fish sauce and 1 teaspoon salt. Use your hands or a fork to fully combine but do not over mix.
2. Use your hands or an ice cream scoop to form 2-inch meatballs (about 2 ounces each). In a large Dutch oven or pot, heat the oil over medium-high heat. Working in batches, add the meatballs in a single layer and cook, flipping halfway through, until golden brown on two sides, 5 to 8 minutes. Transfer to a plate and repeat, adding oil as needed.
3. Once all the meatballs are browned and out of the pot, if the oil is burned, wipe it out and add a bit more to the pot. Reduce the heat to medium, add the reserved ginger mixture and sauté until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add the chicken broth, coconut milk, sugar and the remaining 1 tablespoon fish sauce, and bring to a simmer. Add the meatballs and any juices from the plate, and simmer until the flavours come together and the meatballs are cooked through, 5 to 8 minutes.

One pot wonders are definitely my thing! They’re easy, less messy than other recipes, and always deliver huge flavour! 💯

This recipe comes from the queen🫅herself, @jessseinfeld . I just swapped the peas for edamame + corn, and added some sautéed bacon at the start of the recipe to really boost up that flavor! It’s totally optional but OH SO GOOD! 😋

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* 3 pieces, thick cut bacon, chopped (optional)
* 8-10 small chicken thighs (skin on bone in)

* ¼ tsp freshly ground black pepper
* 1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil
* 3 cloves garlic, chopped
* 1 tsp grated lemon zest (from 1 lemon)
* 8 sprigs fresh thyme (or 2 tsp chopped dill)
* 1 1/2 cups brown rice
* 2 cups chicken broth
* 1 cup water

Make it! 
* Pat the chicken dry with paper towels. Season the chicken with the salt and pepper
* Heat a large pot with a tight fitting lid.

* Add back your chicken thighs, nestling them into the rice mixture.

What you’ll need: 
Cake:
* 6 room temperature eggs
* 1/4 cup white sugar
* 1 or 2 packets (95 grams) chocolate pudding powder
Cream layer:
* 2 cups heavy whipping cream
* 3/4 cup milk (I used 1%)
* 1 or 2 packets (95 grams) vanilla pudding powder
Chocolate top:
* 1 cup semi sweet chocolate chips
* 1 tbsp coconut oil
Make it: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* Preheat oven to 350°F.
* Start by separating your egg whites from the yolks into two different bowls.
* Using a mixer with a whip attachment, whip the egg whites, starting on low for a few minutes. Sprinkle in a pinch of salt.
* Up the speed to medium and slowly start to add in the sugar, little by little until it becomes fluffy (5 minutes total).
* Remove from mixer and gradually fold in some of your egg yolks, followed by the chocolate pudding powder, alternating the two until complete. Fold until well combined.
* Use butter or oil spray and prepare your 11 inch round pan.
* Poor in the batter, smoothing the top and placed into the oven for 20 minutes.
* Meanwhile, wash and dry you’re mixing bowl. 
* In the clean bowl add the whipping cream, milk and vanilla pudding packets. Whip, starting off slow, then medium and then high for about five minutes. After five minutes, it should be thick and creamy.
* Once cake has cooled, transferred to a serving dish. (Should slide right out, easy)
* Using a spatula, spread whip cream topping all over cake, including sides. Place in the fridge to stay cool.
* Place your chocolate chips and coconut oil in a microwave safe bowl and microwave for increments of 30 seconds until melted.
* Or chocolate over cake and smooth it out, covering all edges.
* Place in the fridge for at least 10 minutes, just to solidify the chocolate topping.

Have you ever tried Israeli Couscous? 🇮🇱🍚 This tiny rice like pasta is sooo delicious, my kids ask for it all the time! It’s chewy, nutty and ready in no time and pairs nicely with almost any dish! ⁣
But wait…, have you ever tried toasting it first?! 🤨 GAMECHANGER! 💯 ⁣
This is a must make side dish! 🤤 ⁣
Make it today in honour of Israel’s 75 birthday! ⁣
Chag Sameach! Happy Independence Day 🇮🇱🇮🇱⁣🇮🇱
⁣
What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
* 2 tbsp olive oil⁣
* 1 cup pearl couscous⁣
* 1 ½ cups water⁣
* Kosher salt⁣
* 1 sweet onion, sliced in half moons⁣
* chopped fresh parsley (optional)⁣
⁣
Make it: ⁣
* In a large saucepan, heat 2 tbsp olive oil over medium heat until just shiny. Add the couscous and toss around to coat in oil.⁣
* Keep moving the couscous while it starts to turn golden brown (4-5 minutes).⁣
* Boil water and add the toasted couscous. Season with kosher salt. Bring to a boil, then turn the heat to low. ⁣
* Cover and cook for about 14 minutes or until the pearl couscous is tender.⁣
* Meanwhile, fry up your onion in a little bit of olive oil, until soft and caramelized. ⁣
* When couscous is cooked and done, add in the caramelized onion and mix well.⁣
* Taste and adjust salt to your liking. Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.⁣
⁣
Enjoy! #wiseEATS😘⁣

Panzanella is summer in a bowl! 🥗🍞 
This salad combines quality tomatoes and fresh summer veggies with chunks of vinaigrette soaked crusty bread, making for the most delicious summer salad! 🤤💯 

This time around I used @miette_boulangerie sourdough croutons, and they did not disappoint! 🍞💯

If you can’t get your hands on those, I put instructions on how to make your own! 😋 

What you’ll need: 
* 2 tbsp olive oil
* 3-4 slices of good crusty bread, (sourdough, ciabatta, baguette), cubed 
* 2-3 heirloom tomatoes, cut into chunks
* 6-7 cocktail tomatoes, halved
* 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, whole
* 2-3 Lebanese cucumber, or one long, English cucumber, unpeeled and slice
* 1 red bell pepper, seeded and cut into 1-inch cubes
* 1/4 red onion, cut in 1/2 and thinly sliced
* 2-3 radishes, sliced thinly
* 10 basil leaves, coarsely chopped
Vinaigrette:
* 1/4 red wine vinegar
* 1 garlic, pressed
* 1 tsp sea salt
* 3/4 cup extra virgin olive oil

Make it: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* Heat oil in a large sauté pan. Add the cubes bread and cook over low to medium heat, tossing frequently, for 10 minutes, or until nicely browned. Add more oil as needed. Sprinkle with some salt.
* Meanwhile, whisk all the ingredients together for the vinaigrette.
* In a large bowl, mix the tomatoes, cucumber, red pepper, red onion, radish and basil. 
* Add the toasted and cooled bread cubes, and toss with the vinaigrette. 
* Season with salt and pepper. 
* Serve, or let the salad sit for a bit blend the flavours and let the bread really soak up the juices.

Enjoy! 😘 #wiseEATS

7. Set dipped raspberries on the parchment paper lined baking sheet. ⁣
8. Freeze until serving.⁣ Store in the freezer.

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* 1 tbsp neutral oil, (avocado, I used olive oil)
* 1 onion, sliced
* 2 handfuls of mushrooms, (shiitake, cremini, button etc..) stems removed + sliced
* 1 tbsp fresh grated ginger 
* 4 garlic cloves, minced
* 4 cups low sodium chicken broth
* 1 1/2 cup water
* 1/3 - 1/2 cup low sodium soy sauce (start with 1/3 cup and add 2 tbsp if you feel the need)
* 1/4 cup rice vinegar
* 2 tbsp oyster sauce
* 1 tbsp fish sauce
* 1 tbsp, sambal chili sauce (omit or use less ‘cause this makes it hot!)
* 6-8 baby bok choy sliced into quarters lengthwise
* Handful of snow peas
* Handful of kale/spinach 
* 1-2 packages ramen noodles 
* 12 shrimps, premartinated from @lemaitreboucher or seasoned by you!
* Chicken dumpling 🥟 (optional from @nationalfoodshop)
Toppings: green onion Gomasio (sesame seeds) available @naturesante 
Let’s make it!
* Heat a large pot on medium high heat. 
* Add the onion and sauté until soften, about 5 minutes. Add the sliced mushrooms if using and sauté for another 2-3 minutes. Next add the garlic and ginger and stir fry for about 30 seconds, just until fragrant so that they don’t burn. 
* Add chicken broth and 1 1/2 cups of water. Then add soy sauce, rice vinegar, oyster sauce, fish sauce, sambal if using, and stir to combine. Bring back to a simmer, a leave on low while you prepare the noodles and shrimps.
* Prepare ramen noodles according to package instructions.
* Grill shrimps on a grill pan, 2-3 minutes a side.
* Once shrimps are cooked, add the bok choy, snow peas and kale to the broth and cook for 3-5 minutes. 
* Remove from heat assemble your soup! Start with an empty bowl and add in your noodles. Then ladle soup over and top with shrimps, dumplings, green onion and gomasio! Enjoy!

Chocolate Hazelnut Blackberry Bark 🍫🌰🫐⁣
If you love a quick snack or sweet treat, this bark is a way better option than Ferraro Rocher…. it’s also wayyyyy healthier 💯⁣
I used @itsnutterie fresh hazelnuts and unsweetened coconut shreds 🥥! @itsnutterie is proudly eco-conscious and sustainable and their nuts, dried fruits, and seeds are ethically sourced directly from local farmers, fresh to your table. 😋 They also taste incredible!! Try @itsnutterie today and save 15% off your orders at checkout with code MARTA15 🥳⁣
⁣
What you’ll need:⁣ 👩🏻‍🍳 
* 1 cup @itsnutterie blanched hazelnuts⁣
* 2 full bars of semi-sweet chocolate (I used Bakers but you can use 2 cups of chocolate chips)⁣
* 1 tsp coconut oil⁣
* 3/4 cup blackberries⁣
* Handful of @itsnutterie coconut shreds⁣
* Maldon sea salt⁣
⁣
Make it:⁣
* Start by preheating your oven to 275°F
* Grab a small baking sheet and pour on your hazelnuts. Roast for 20 minutes. (Allow to cool completely before making the rest!)⁣
* Meanwhile, wash and dry your blackberries very well.⁣
* Prepare your chocolate by adding it to a microwave safe bowl and adding in the coconut oil. Place the microwave for 25 seconds at a time. Do this about 3 times until the chocolate is melted and runs smooth. (You can also do this over the stove top in a double boiler.) ⁣
* When the toasted hazelnuts have cooled, push them to one side of the cookie sheet so they are close together. ⁣
* Drizzle half the melted chocolate over hazelnuts and then strategically place the blackberries in between the nuts.⁣
* Top with more melted chocolate to smother the blackberries.⁣
* Top with fresh coconut shreds and some Malden sea salt.⁣
* Allow the chocolate to set completely by placing in the freezer for 1 hour.⁣
* Once the chocolate has set, break the bark into pieces of your desired size. ⁣
* Store in the freezer 🥶 ⁣
⁣

Say 👋 to this super crispy and refreshing green juice 💚 all made in my blender! Juice in a blender you ask? How can that be!? 🤔 Oh it CAN be, and it’s up in stories today!  This time I used two sieve strainers, but what you really need is a nut milk bag. 🥤🌿😜⁣
Recipe I made was just what I had in my fridge,  so it’s really open to whatever greens you’ve got... the possibilities are endless! ⁣
Btw... it’s definitely kid tested, mother approved!🙌🏼⁣
Happy juicing! 💚⁣
⁣
BLENDER GREEN JUICE 🌿💚🌿⁣
⁣
What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
🌿½ cup filtered water⁣
🌿5-7 stalks of celery chopped into 2 inch pieces ⁣
🌿3-4 leaves kale 🌿(with stems)⁣
🌿½ large English cucumber 🥒(skin on if organic)⁣
🌿1 granny smith apple 🍏 (no core) ⁣
🌿small peice of pineapple for sweetness 🍍 ⁣
🌿bunch of cilantro or parsley (optional)⁣
🌿juice of one lemon 🍋 ⁣
🌿optional add in’s - mint, ginger, fennel and  lime juice⁣
⁣
Make it: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
💚 Add filtered water and all your greens + fruits to high-powered blender like a @vitamixca. Make sure to reserve the lemon 🍋 for after blending.⁣
💚 Blend on high for 30 seconds or until everything becomes smooth. 💡(Do this in batches if you find that your blender is over packed. Once you start to blend, everything will come down in size, leaving more room for you to add more greens and fruits).⁣
💚 Using a chip clip or a clothesline pin, clip one side of the nut milk bag to the side of a large bowl. Using your hand, hold the other side of the bag open wide, while you pour the pulp filled mixture in. ⁣
💚Squeeze the bag in a milking fashion 😜, until all the juice is in the bowl, and only the pulp remains in the bag. ⁣
💚Squeeze in the juice of one lemon 🍋 ⁣
💚Pour the mixture over a glass full of ice and enjoy right away! ⁣
YUMMMMMM! 👌🏼⁣
⁣
Enjoy! #wiseEATS😘⁣

A little bit of nature’s candy 🍭 for dinner last night! Light and delicious, yet super feeling and healthy AF! These mini butternut squash are absolutely delicious! 🤤 
This is a must try recipe! Even my kids were gobbling it up!!
Make it! 💯 

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* 1 baby butternut squash 
* 2 tbsp olive oil
* 2 tbsp tamari 
* 1 tsp maple syrup 
* 1/2 tsp kosher salt
* 1/2 tsp pepper
* 1/2 tsp garlic powder
* 1/2 tsp onion powder

Make it: 
* Preheat oven to 425°F. convection bake if you have it.
* In a small bowl, combine all of the ingredients above (except the squash, of course!).

This little spice rub will make your whole dinner. Trust me! 💯 
Make this and sprinkle it over fish, a whole cauliflower, and even over those baby potatoes. SO YUM!
🐟🥔🥦

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
Spice rub:
* 2 tbsp brown sugar
* 2 tsp smoked paprika
* 2 tsp onion powder
* 1 tsp garlic powder
* 1/2 tsp chili powder
* 1/2 tsp kosher salt 
* 2 tbsp olive oil
Salmon: 
* Salmon filtet
* Olive oil
* Chopped mango
* Chopped avocado
Whole Roasted Cauliflower:
* 1 whole cauliflower head 
* 1/4 cup extra virgin olive oil 
* spice rub 
Potatoes:
* 1 lbs baby potatoes
* Olive oil
Make it:
* Preheat the oven to 400°F and place a rack in the middle position.
* Bring a pot of water to a boil. Once boiling, submerge the entire cauliflower into the pot and let boil for 5 minutes.
* Remove cauliflower carefully from water and place on a cookie sheet fitted with a metal baking tray. Let it sit and dry off for at least 20 to 25 minutes.
* Meanwhile, combine all the spice rub ingredients into a shallow bowl or plate. Once mixed well, take each filet of salmon and press it into the spice mixture to fully coat each fillet. Place on a prepared baking sheet fitted with parchment paper. Repeat with all your filets and then drizzle with a little bit of olive oil. Set aside.
* Next, drizzle olive oil all over the cooled cauliflower and with your hands, rub the oil all over the surface (both top and bottom) until the cauliflower is well coated. Season both sides of the cauliflower liberally with spice rub. Place the cauliflower florets-side up on a large baking sheet.
* In a small bowl, add in your baby potatoes and cover in 1 tbsp of olive oil. Season potatoes with about 1 tbsp of the spice mixture. Toss well to make sure they’re well coated. Now pour them all around the cauliflower. Place cauliflower and potatoes on the middle rack, and place prepared salmon fillets on the rack just below. Bake all together for 30 minutes uncovered.
* Once the cauliflower is golden brown on the outside, take it out of the oven. 
* Remove fish from oven and place each fillet on a plate and cover with chopped avocado and mango. Serve with cauliflower and potatoes.

Enjoy! #wiseEATS😘

This is the perfect summer salad! 🌽 🥗⁣ 💯 
While the corn is still delicious, I highly suggest you guys make this one! 💯 If bacon is not your thing, just omit, but if it’s your thing,… Well, you already know it’s delicious lol 🥓 ⁣
Make THIS! ⁣
⁣
What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
* 12 slices bacon, chopped⁣
* 9-10 ears fresh corn, kernels cut from the cob⁣
* 3 cups baby arugula⁣
* 2 cup cherry tomatoes , halved or quartered⁣
* 1/2 cup fresh basil, chopped ⁣
* 1/2 cup olive oil⁣
* 6 tbsp red wine vinegar⁣
*  1 tsp kosher salt⁣
*  1 tsp freshly ground black pepper⁣
⁣
Make it:⁣
* Start by cutting the corn off the cob. Set all the niblets aside. ⁣
* Next, quarter or half your cherry tomatoes. Set aside.⁣
* Heat a large skillet over medium heat and add the chopped bacon. Cook until the bacon is crisped and the fat is rendered. Use a slotted spoon to transfer the bacon to a plate lined with a paper towel to drain. ⁣
* Meanwhile, make the vinaigrette. Add red wine vinegar kosher salt and pepper, and slowly whisk in the olive oil to emulsify.⁣
* In a large bowl, toss the corn kernels with the bacon, arugula, cherry tomatoes, and basil. Drizzle with the vinaigrette. Toss to coat and serve at room temperature or chilled.⁣

* In a jar, add all spices. Shake + store in an airtight container. (Use 2 tbsp of seasoning per 1 lb of ground meat when making taco meat).

Pico de Gallo 🍅 
* 1 pint grape tomatoes, quartered/2 tbsp roughly chopped cilantro leaves/3 tbsp finely chopped white onion/coarse salt/squeeze of lime/1 jalapeño chopped
* Combine the tomatoes, cilantro, jalapeño and onion together in a bowl. Season to taste with salt and lime.

The other night I was hardcore craving PASTA 🤤🤤🤤… Not like a tomato sauce style pasta, but more of a sausage kinda pasta using tons of veggies from the fridge. In the past I’ve dubbed this pasta the “kitchen sink”, ‘cause you can really put anything and everything you want! 
This is one of my go-to recipes when I am short on time and want to use up what I’ve got in the house. This time I used turkey sausage with some leftover steak from the night before, fresh corn off the cob, shallots, leeks, mushrooms, arugula, spinach, and even some roasted cauliflower and zucchini. Topped it with freshly shredded Parmesan cheese and voila! Dinner is served! 
MAKE IT! 🤤 
What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳
* 1 Tbsp olive oil
* 1 lbs turkey sausage, decades
* 2 shallots, minced
* 1 leek sliced in half moon (Top and bottom removed)
* 5-7 cremini mushrooms, sliced
* 3 garlics, minced
* 1/2 tsp each salt, pepper and garlic powder, onion powder
* 3 ears of corn, kernels cut off
* 1 1/2 cup chicken stock
* 2 handfuls of arugula
* 2 handfuls of spinach
* 1 cup roasted cauliflower florets
* 1 cup roasted zucchini
* 1 lbs pasta, any shape

Make it
1. Start by preparing and roasting the cauliflower and zucchini. Toss florets and zucchini pieces with with olive oil, salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion powder. Roast in the oven at 425 F for 15-20 minutes. When ready, remove from oven and set aside.
2. Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package instructions. DON’T FORGET to salt the water and reserve 1 cup of pasta water before draining!!!
3. Set a large stockpot to medium high heat, de-case the sausage and fry until crispy. When done, remove from pan and set aside.
4. To the already dirty pot, add 1 tbsp of olive oil and start sautéing the shallots and leeks. Cook for a few minutes before adding in the mushrooms and then garlic. Cook for an additional minute and then season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion powder.
5. Next, pour in the corn niblets and sauté for a few minutes more.
6. Cover in chicken stock and bring to a boil. Once boiling, reduce to a simmer and start to scape the bottom of the pan, lifting all those yummy brown bits of flavour.

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
* 1 lbs rigatoni pasta⁣
* 1/2 cup of olive oil⁣
* 1 onion, diced ⁣
* 4 corn on the cob, kernels only⁣
* 6 garlic cloves⁣
* 2 tsp kosher salt (plus more if you feel the need)⁣
* 1 tsp sugar⁣
* 1 tbsp kewpie mayo⁣
* 2 cup of water⁣
* 1/2 tsp sweet paprika⁣
* 1/2 cup grated cheddar⁣
* 1 cup grated parmesan⁣
* 1/2 cup shredded mozzarella⁣
Toppings:⁣
* Chill crisp⁣
* Torn cilantro ⁣
* Chopped green onion ⁣
⁣
Make it:⁣
* Start by cooking the pasta according to package instructions. Before draining, save a cup of pasta water (just incase!!). When pasta is al dente, drain and set aside.⁣
* In a large pot on medium heat, add olive oil, whole garlics, diced onions, and corn and sauté until the onions are soft and  transparent, about 5 minutes. ⁣
* Add in the salt, sugar, mayo, water, and paprika and bring to a boil. Once boiling, reduce to a simmer and covered for about 20 minutes.⁣
* After the 20 minutes are up, pour the entire pot into a blender and blend until smooth. ⁣
* Next, add blended corn sauce back into the pot on medium heat. Add the cooked pasta and all the cheeses.⁣
* Mix until the cheese have completely melted and the sauce is smooth. If need be, add a touch of pasta water.⁣
* Portion into bowls and top with chili crisp, cilantro, and scallions. DROOOOOOL⁣

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* 3-4 medium granny smith apples (or honey crisp, pink lady)
* 1 tbsp pure maple syrup
* 3 tbsp water
* 2 tsp cinnamon

Crumble Topping
* 1 cup @itsnutterie organic oats
* 1/2 cup almond flour 
* 1/2 cup chopped almonds/walnuts/pecans (optional)
* 1 tsp cinnamon
* 1 tsp @kanel organic cacao apple crisp spice (option)
* 1/4 tsp salt
* 1/4 cup melted coconut oil
* 1/4 cup maple syrup

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳

* 1 cup broccoli, chopped into small florets
* 1 cup cauliflower, chopped into small florets
* 1 zucchini, cut in quarters

‘Tis is the season my friends! It’s time to indulge in one of my most favourite FRIED treats... LATKES! 🕎 🥔 ✡️
I took my latke dreams to extra fancy heights this year with the addition of crème fraîche, caviar and chives 🤤 🤤 🤤 (swipe to second pic)…

Happy Hanukkah friends 😘 

What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 
* 2 lbs russet potatoes (about 4-5 large) peeled and cut lengthwise
* 1 yellow onion, sliced in half
* 1/2 cup matzo meal
* 2 tsp kosher salt
* 4 eggs
* Grapeseed oil, for frying
* @kitehill chive cream cheese available @naturesante, or sour cream
* Apple sauce
* Maldon sea salt
* Toppings: crème fresh, smoke salmon, chives, applesauce, caviar of choice 

Make it:
1. Wash, peel and slice your potatoes lengthwise.
2. Using a food processor fitted with the medium grating attachment, grate together potatoes and onion. (if you do not have food food processor, use a box grater.
3. Transfer mixture to a big bowl lined with dish towel, and wring out potatoes and onion. Try your best to squeeze out any and all liquid. 
4. Let the liquid sit for 5 minutes so that the starch milkiness can drop to the bottom. 
5. THE SECRET TO THE CRUNCH ➡️ 💫Pour off liquid leaving the white milky bottom and potato/onion mixture back into bowl 💫 
6. Add in the eggs, matzah meal and salt. Mix until well incorporated.
7. Heat 1/4 inch of grapeseed oil in a large cast iron or nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Working in batches, scoop 1/4 cup balls of latke mixture and drop into pan. Using a flat spatula, gently push the latkes to flatten. 
8. Cook, flipping once, until golden, 2-3 minutes per side, then transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to drain.
9. Sprinkle with Maldon sea salt and top with ALL THE THINGS! 

Enjoy! 😘 #wiseEATS and HAPPY 🕎!!!

If you haven’t been able to tell from all my other recipe posts, I REALLY like using ground chicken🐔! It requires no cutting, no bones and cooks super fast! 💨 
This time I used it to make the fan favourite General Tso’s Chicken!! 🍲 These bowls were too delicious! Kids devoured! 💯 
Wants know the best part? The whole thing was made in☝🏼pan, and ready in 20 minutes!!! 💥 

Make this now!

General Tso sauce:
* 2/3 cup coconut aminos (or 1/3 coconut aminos + 1/3 light soy sauce)
* 4 tbsp rice vinegar 
* 4 tbsp chicken broth (not pictured in reel)
* 2 tbsp hoisin sauce
* 2 tsp coconut sugar
* 2 tsp garlic powder
* 1 tsp fresh grated ginger 
* 2 tsp cornstarch or arrowroot starch
* Salt and pepper 

* 1 tbsp avocado oil
* 1 whole broccoli cut into mini florets + stems
* 2 lb ground chicken
* Chopped green onions
* Sesame seeds

Make it: (serves 6)
* Start by combining the ingredients for the sauce in a bowl and mix well. Set aside.
* Heat avocado oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. 
* Add chopped broccoli and stems to pan and saute for 5 minutes or until lightly crisp and cooked. Season with a little salt and pepper and then remove from the pan and set aside.
* Add the ground chicken to the same pan and break up using a wooden spoon. Saute until fully cooked and you no longer see any pink. 
* Add broccoli back to the pan and pour over the General Tso sauce. Reduce the heat to low and continue to stir until the sauce thickens and fully coats the chicken and broccoli.
* Garnish with sesame seeds and green onions and serve over Jasmin or sushi rice!

Mayak eggs are Korean marinated eggs that are first soft boiled, then marinated overnight in a delicious soy and honey based mixture. These eggs are otherwise know as “drug eggs” for being so addictive and delicious 🤤 ⁣
They’re great for breakfast, lunch or even just to snack on!⁣
⁣
Make them!⁣
⁣
What you’ll need: 👩🏻‍🍳 ⁣
Egg marinade: 🫙⁣
* 1/2 cup soy sauce ⁣
* 1/2 cup water⁣
* 1/4 cup honey⁣
* 1/4 onion diced⁣
* 1 green onion, diced⁣
* 3 cloves garlic, minced⁣
* 2 jalapeño, diced⁣
* 1 tbsp toasted sesame seeds⁣
* Sesame oil for topping⁣
Egg prep: 🥚 ⁣
* 6 eggs (make sure they are at room temperature)⁣
* 1 tbsp salt⁣
* 1 tbsp white vinegar⁣
* sesame oil for garnish⁣
* Sesame seeds for garnish⁣
⁣
Make it:⁣
* Add all the marinade ingredients into a large bowl. Mix well to combine and set aside.⁣
* Add 1 tbsp of vinegar and and 1 tbsp of salt to a pot of boiling water. ⁣
* Reduce the heat to simmer and place eggs into the water. Simmer for 6 minutes (for jammy- otherwise 10 minutes for hard boiled).⁣
* Prepare a large bowl of ice water.⁣
* When eggs are done cooking, immediately transfer them to the ice water. Allow the eggs to cool for at least 5 minutes. ⁣
* Gently peel the eggs and add them to the marinade. ⁣
* Cover tightly and store in the refrigerator overnight. ⁣
* To serve, place the egg over a bed of rice and top with a touch of sesame oil and sesame seeds.⁣
Enjoy! ⁣
